## Welcome

### Aims

This workbook contains some of the material relating to Epigenetic Epidemiology covered in the University of Bristol's unit Molecular Epidemiology of Non-communicable Disease (unit 8 of the MSc in Epidemiology). It is designed to help students achieve the following Intended Learning Outcomes:

*   Give examples of how epigenetic data can be used in epidemiological studies of non-communicable disease, including appropriate study design and analysis strategy
*   Describe the design and challenges of epigenome-wide association studies
*   Interpret results from epigenome-wide association studies
*   Critically evaluate scientific papers that use epigenetic data to study non-communicable disease

## 1. Epigenetics & Epidemiology {.tabset}

