The live session will also give you an opportunity to ask any questions about the online material or bring up any points for discussion. You can save any such questions for the live session, or you can post them (anonymously) on this [padlet](https://padlet.com/gs8094/5vvz4eu7dyyhpwx7).

### How to read a paper


Prior to the live session, please watch the following video:

![](https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=H3aaXOrlAyg)

### Read and critically appraise an EWAS paper


Prior to the live session, please read this paper:

Cardona et al. (2019) Epigenome-Wide Association Study of Incident Type 2 Diabetes in a British Population: EPIC-Norfolk Study, *Diabetes*;68(12):2315-2326. https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/31506343

(remember, you do not have to critically appraise the MR element of this paper)

And answer the following questions:
*Keep a note of your answers - your group will need these during the live session*

*   **General study design**
    +   What study design was used?
    +   What were the aims of the study?
    +   What exposures? 
    +   What outcomes? 
    +   What population?
    +   Was the study sample representative of the defined population? 
    +   Was there something special about the sample? 
    +   Was everyone included who should have been? 
  
*   **Measurement of the exposure**
    +   How did they measure the exposure? 
    +   Was the exposure accurately measured to minimise bias? 
    +   Was the exposure measured in the same way for all participants? 

*   **Measurement of the outcome**
    +   How did they measure the outcome? 
    +   Was the outcome accurately measured to minimise bias? 
    +   Was the outcome measured in the same way for all participants? 
    +   If the study design is prospective, was the follow-up of participants long enough and complete enough? 
  
*   **Consideration of confounders** 
    +   Have the authors identified all important confounding factors? 
    +   How have they taken account of the confounding factors in the design or analysis? 

*   **Interpretation of results** 
    +   What are the results of this study? 
    +   How large are the effect estimates? 
    +   How precise are the results? 
    +   Is this study credible, I.e. do you believe the results? 

*   **What does this study add?** 
    +   Do the results of this study fit with other available evidence? 
    +   What are the implications of this study for future research? 
    +   What are the implications of this study for clinical practice or public health (if any) 
  
